ðŸ“– **Description:**
    The `eqn` command is used to format mathematical equations in text files. It helps you to create complex mathematical expressions in a printable format. It reads equations from the terminal or specified files and outputs the result in troff or eqn language.

âš™ï¸ **Options:**
    ðŸ”¹ `eqn -d xy`  --> âœï¸ Change the delimiters used to mark mathematical equations. By default, the delimiters are `.` and `.` . In this example, `x` and `y` replace the delimiters.
    ðŸ”¹ `eqn -f font` --> âœ’ï¸ Use a specific font for the mathematical equations.
    ðŸ”¹ `eqn -r`      --> ðŸ”„ Enable auto-sizing. This option helps to automatically align sizes of the components.
    ðŸ”¹ `eqn -T name`  --> ðŸ–¥ï¸ Prepare the output for a specific device (name).

