    $ eqn file.eqn | troff -ms

    ðŸ”¹ Execute eqn on file.eqn and then pipe the output to troff for processing and final output generation.

    $ eqn -d '$ $' equation.txt | troff -ms

    ðŸ”¹ In this example, `$` is used as the delimiter. The `eqn` command processes the equations in `equation.txt` and sends the output to `troff`.

